snippet.textDisplay:
Not too bad a loss for the Clippers. 76ers by far the best Home team this year at 25 Wins 2 Losses, and Clippers kept it close despite Paul George having just 13 Points on 48 possible Points. PG having a terrible night was the the difference on the Clips side.

But huge win for the 76ers. Embiid looked great, and, more importantly, confident. And solid night for Simmons and RIchardson -- all 3 guys out 20 Pts and had a better game that either PG or Morris and Williams -- second best Clipper tonight was Shamet off the bench. But Embiid, Simmons, Richardson, and Harris were all solid. That's how they need to play on the road and improve that 9 W 19 L road record.
